## Problem
The Vite plan focused on JS but ignored CSS. Current CSS structure:
- static/css/app.css - Main app styles
- static/css/themes.css - Theme variables
- static/css/themes/*.css - Individual theme files
- static/css/font-fix.css - Font overrides
- static/lib/stroke-7/style.css - Icon font

## Goals
- Bundle CSS with Vite
- Enable CSS imports in JS modules
- Add PostCSS for autoprefixer
- Maintain theme switching functionality

## Implementation Steps

### 1. Install CSS tooling
```bash
npm install --save-dev postcss autoprefixer cssnano
```

### 2. Create postcss.config.js
```javascript
export default {
  plugins: {
    autoprefixer: {},
    cssnano: process.env.NODE_ENV === 'production' ? {} : false
  }
};
```

### 3. Update vite.config.js for CSS
```javascript
export default defineConfig({
  css: {
    postcss: './postcss.config.js',
    devSourcemap: true,
  },
  build: {
    cssCodeSplit: true,  // Separate CSS per entry point
    rollupOptions: {
      input: {
        main: resolve(__dirname, 'static/js/main.js'),
        // CSS entry points
        styles: resolve(__dirname, 'static/css/main.css'),
      }
    }
  }
});
```

### 4. Create main CSS entry point
```css
/* static/css/main.css */
@import './app.css';
@import './themes.css';
@import './font-fix.css';
@import '../lib/stroke-7/style.css';
```

### 5. Handle theme CSS files
Theme files need to stay separate for dynamic loading. Options:

**Option A: Keep themes as separate files (Recommended)**
```javascript
// vite.config.js
import { glob } from 'glob';

const themeFiles = glob.sync('static/css/themes/*.css');
const themeInputs = {};
themeFiles.forEach(file => {
  const name = path.basename(file, '.css');
  themeInputs[`theme-${name}`] = resolve(__dirname, file);
});

export default defineConfig({
  build: {
    rollupOptions: {
      input: {
        main: '...',
        ...themeInputs
      }
    }
  }
});
```

**Option B: CSS custom properties (future enhancement)**
Use CSS variables for theming instead of separate files.

### 6. Import CSS in JS modules (optional)
```javascript
// In main.js
import '../css/main.css';

// Component-specific CSS
// In cluster_explorer/index.js
import './cluster-explorer.css';
```

### 7. Update Django templates
```html
{% load vite %}
<link rel="stylesheet" href="{% vite_asset 'styles.css' %}">
```

### 8. Update theme switcher for Vite builds
The theme switcher loads CSS dynamically. Update to use Vite manifest:
```javascript
function loadTheme(themeName) {
  const link = document.getElementById('theme-css');
  // In dev: /static/css/themes/${themeName}.css
  // In prod: /static/dist/theme-${themeName}-[hash].css
  link.href = getThemeUrl(themeName);
}
```

