## Problem
No mechanism to alert when users encounter JavaScript errors in the browser. Errors fail silently.

## Current State
- Toastr shows user-facing messages but doesn't report to server
- No `window.onerror` handler
- No `unhandledrejection` handler for Promise errors
- No error tracking service (Sentry, Rollbar, etc.)

## Solution: Add Sentry

### 1. Install Sentry SDK
```bash
pip install sentry-sdk[django]
npm install @sentry/browser  # For Vite bundle
```

### 2. Configure Django Sentry (config/settings.py)
```python
import sentry_sdk
from sentry_sdk.integrations.django import DjangoIntegration
from sentry_sdk.integrations.celery import CeleryIntegration

sentry_sdk.init(
    dsn=os.environ.get("SENTRY_DSN"),
    integrations=[
        DjangoIntegration(),
        CeleryIntegration(),
    ],
    traces_sample_rate=0.1,  # 10% of requests
    send_default_pii=True,
    environment=os.environ.get("SENTRY_ENVIRONMENT", "production"),
)
```

### 3. Add Frontend Sentry (static/js/sentry.js)
```javascript
import * as Sentry from '@sentry/browser';

Sentry.init({
  dsn: window.SENTRY_DSN,  // Set from Django template
  environment: window.SENTRY_ENVIRONMENT,
  integrations: [
    Sentry.browserTracingIntegration(),
  ],
  tracesSampleRate: 0.1,
});

// Add user context if logged in
if (window.USER_ID) {
  Sentry.setUser({ id: window.USER_ID, email: window.USER_EMAIL });
}
```

### 4. Add global error handler (fallback for non-Sentry)
```javascript
// static/js/utils/error-handler.js
window.onerror = function(msg, url, lineNo, columnNo, error) {
  console.error('Global error:', { msg, url, lineNo, columnNo, error });
  // Sentry captures this automatically if configured
  return false;
};

window.addEventListener('unhandledrejection', function(event) {
  console.error('Unhandled promise rejection:', event.reason);
});
```

### 5. Update base.html to include Sentry config
```html
<script>
  window.SENTRY_DSN = "{{ SENTRY_DSN }}";
  window.SENTRY_ENVIRONMENT = "{{ SENTRY_ENVIRONMENT }}";
  {% if user.is_authenticated %}
  window.USER_ID = "{{ user.id }}";
  window.USER_EMAIL = "{{ user.email }}";
  {% endif %}
</script>
```

