## Problem
Production errors in minified JS are unreadable:
```
TypeError: Cannot read property 'x' of undefined
    at e (main-abc123.js:1:23456)
```

Need source maps for debugging, but security concerns about exposing them.

## Solution Options

### Option A: Hidden Source Maps (Recommended)
Generate source maps but don't serve them publicly. Upload to error tracking service.

```javascript
// vite.config.js
export default defineConfig({
  build: {
    sourcemap: 'hidden',  // Generates .map files but doesn't reference them in output
  }
});
```

### Option B: External Source Maps
Serve from separate, protected location.

### Option C: No Source Maps
Not recommended for production debugging.

## Implementation (Option A: Hidden Source Maps)

### 1. Configure Vite for hidden source maps
```javascript
// vite.config.js
export default defineConfig({
  build: {
    sourcemap: process.env.NODE_ENV === 'production' ? 'hidden' : true,
    rollupOptions: {
      output: {
        // Keep source map filenames predictable
        sourcemapFileNames: '[name]-[hash].js.map',
      }
    }
  }
});
```

### 2. Set up Sentry (or similar) for error tracking
```bash
npm install --save-dev @sentry/vite-plugin
```

```javascript
// vite.config.js
import { sentryVitePlugin } from '@sentry/vite-plugin';

export default defineConfig({
  plugins: [
    sentryVitePlugin({
      org: 'your-org',
      project: 'battycoda',
      authToken: process.env.SENTRY_AUTH_TOKEN,
      sourcemaps: {
        assets: './static/dist/**',
      },
    }),
  ],
  build: {
    sourcemap: true,  // Sentry plugin handles hiding
  }
});
```

### 3. Alternative: Manual source map upload
If not using Sentry, upload maps manually:
```bash
# scripts/upload-sourcemaps.sh
#!/bin/bash
# Upload source maps to your error tracking service

MAPS_DIR="static/dist"
for map in $MAPS_DIR/*.map; do
  echo "Uploading $map..."
  # curl to your service
done

# Delete source maps from deploy (don't serve them)
rm -f $MAPS_DIR/*.map
```

### 4. Add to deployment script
```bash
# scripts/deploy.sh
npm run build

# Upload source maps to error tracking
./scripts/upload-sourcemaps.sh

# Collect static (maps already removed)
python manage.py collectstatic --noinput
```

### 5. For development: keep source maps enabled
```javascript
// vite.config.js
export default defineConfig({
  build: {
    sourcemap: process.env.NODE_ENV === 'production' 
      ? 'hidden'   // Production: generate but hide
      : true       // Development: inline
  }
});
```

## Without External Service
If not using Sentry/similar, you can still use source maps for debugging:

### Local debugging with production build
```bash
# Keep maps locally for debugging
npm run build
# Maps are in static/dist/*.map

# When debugging production issue:
# 1. Get the minified stack trace
# 2. Use source-map library to decode:
npx source-map resolve static/dist/main-abc123.js.map 1:23456
```

## Security Considerations
- Source maps reveal original code structure
- Don't serve .map files publicly
- Either upload to error service or delete from deploy
- Nginx should block .map files just in case:
```nginx
location ~* \.map$ {
  return 404;
}
```

